se structure on projects — discovers what exists, suggests via template\n- Replace EnterPlanMode — `plan-task` adds principles awareness on top\n- Post comments automatically — output stays in conversation unless user asks\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":5,"timestamp":1772117959,"nonce":"kulwWDcHnVhDNyjn7P4+sE5bQvU=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87uLuaMzwAAAAVhQcWD"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772123657,"nonce":"4JbU0GrN0oMsq9Z9wBrbfpPajMI=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87sfxk7","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/282#issuecomment-3967752507"},"message":"## Lifecycle Workflow Patterns (discovered during #272 implementation)\n\nThe following patterns emerged while testing the triage → plan → implement cycle. Skills in this collection should encode these conventions.\n\n### Triage (triage-issue skill)\n- Output is a **comment on the issue**, not an edit to the issue body\n- Preserves paper trail; issue body remains the authoritative spec\n- Triage is advisory input for the planning agent\n\n### Planning (plan-task skill)\n- Plan is saved to `.agent/work-plans/PLAN_ISSUE-\u003cN\u003e.md` and committed to the feature branch\n- A **draft PR** is opened with the plan as the first commit\n- The PR body summarizes the plan and links to the plan file\n- Copilot (or other reviewers) can review the plan before implementation begins\n\n### Implementation\n- Implementer reads the plan + any review comments on the plan commit\n- Plan review feedback is **incorporated on the fly** during implementation — no separate plan-update cycle\n- The plan file is a starting point, not a contract\n\n### Completion\n- Implementer leaves a **summary comment on the PR** with post-task verification checklist\n- PR is **marked ready for review** (exits draft state)\n- This triggers Copilot review of the implementation (if configured)\n\n### Full sequence\n```\ntriage-issue → comment on issue\nplan-task    → commit plan + open draft PR\nimplement    → commits on same branch, incorporating plan review feedback\ncomplete     → summary comment + mark PR ready\nreview-pr    → evaluate against principles (human or skill)\n```\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772127770,"nonce":"Xx1ss33xTkCdj8AVoE27TsfZha4=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87shXP-","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/282#issuecomment-3968168958"},"message":"## Triage Summary\n\nAll 11 issues have been triaged. Key findings and revised ordering below.\n\n### Status After Triage\n\n| Issue | Title | Triage Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| #271 | Merge principles | **Done** — merged as PR #283 |\n| #272 | Shared evaluation guide | **Done** — PR #285 ready for review |\n| #273 | Governance template | **Wait for #284** — layout depends on `.agents/` unification |\n| #274 | Discovery script | **Ready** — well-scoped, minor cleanup consequences |\n| #275 | gather-project-knowledge | **Blocked** — `project_knowledge` path conflict needs design decision |\n| #276 | review-pr | **Ready** — scope to core single-PR evaluation first |\n| #277 | triage-issue | **Ready** — consider renaming to `review-issue` |\n| #278 | plan-task | **Ready** — clarify: generates plans, not evaluates them |\n| #279 | brainstorm | **Consider deferring** — value proposition unclear vs. natural conversation |\n| #280 | audit-workspace | **Ready** — needs concrete checklist defined |\n| #281 | audit-project | **Consider deferring** — no project governance docs to audit yet |\n\n### New Issues From This Session\n\n| Issue | Title | Relationship |\n|---|---|---|\n| #284 | Unify project agent directories under `.agents/` | Prerequisite for #273, #275; soft dependency for #274 |\n| #286 | Add plan-first workflow guidance to Copilot review instructions | Independent improvement |\n\n### Emerging Themes\n\n1. **#284 is a prerequisite**: The `.agents/` unification decision affects the governance template (#273), discovery script paths (#274), and the `project_knowledge` conflict (#275). Consider prioritizing it.\n\n2. **Several skills lack input data**: #275 (gather-project-knowledge), #279 (brainstorm), #281 (audit-project) have limited value until project repos adopt governance docs. These can be deferred without blocking the core lifecycle.\n\n3. **Core lifecycle is clear**: `review-issue → plan-task → implement → review-pr` — these four skills (#277, #278, #276) plus the review guide (#272) form the immediate-value set.\n\n### Suggested Revised Order\n\n1. ~~#271 — Merge principles~~ ✅\n2. ~~#272 — Evaluation guide~~ ✅ (PR #285)\n3. **#284 — Unify `.agents/`** (unblocks #273, #275)\n4. **#274 — Discovery script** (foundation for skills)\n5. **#273 — Governance template** (after #284)\n6. **#277 — review-issue skill** (most common touchpoint)\n7. **#278 — plan-task skill** (next in lifecycle)\n8. **#276 — review-pr skill** (validates the cycle)\n9. **#280 — audit-workspace** (periodic check)\n10. **#275 — gather-project-knowledge** (after path conflict resolved)\n11. **#279 — brainstorm** (defer until demand)\n12. **#281 — audit-project** (defer until projects have governance)\n13. **#286 — Copilot review instructions** (independent, anytime)\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772144676,"nonce":"dZxxfhmFlMOGYADr6yI6T5R7e8o=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87smxZZ","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/282#issuecomment-3969586777"},"message":"## Verification of completed sub-issues (Feb 2026)\n\nAll 13 sub-issues (including #284 and #286 discovered during triage) are closed. Verified five areas flagged in the triage comments:\n\n### 1. Rename triage-issue → review-issue (#277) — Clean ✓\n\nSkill lives at `.claude/skills/review-issue/`. Commit `272b5c5` explains the rename. One stale reference in archived work plan `PLAN_ISSUE-272.md` — trivial, no action needed.\n\n### 2. Brainstorm skill (#279) \"value unclear\" concern — Addressed ✓\n\nConcern was addressed by pairing brainstorm with a new `research` skill (producer-consumer pattern). Research maintains git-tracked digests; brainstorm consumes them alongside governance context. Copilot review further tightened it by enumerating specific governance sources.\n\n### 3. Audit-project skill (#281) \"no governance docs to audit\" concern — Addressed ✓\n\nSkill handles missing governance gracefully — framed as \"coverage report, not a mandate\" with minimal/standard/full adoption classification. Currently 1/36 projects has governance docs, so it serves as an adoption tracker.\n\n### 4. Lifecycle workflow pattern — Gap found → #302\n\nThe `review-issue → plan-task → implement → review-pr` lifecycle is captured but distributed across individual skill files. No centralized workflow document exists, and `review-issue`/`review-pr` lack explicit lifecycle position labels. Opened #302 to track.\n\n### 5. Project knowledge path conflict (#275 via #284) — Incomplete\n\nPR #284 created a symlink (`.agent/project_knowledge/` → `.agents/workspace-context/`) but didn't update all references. Core docs (AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, copilot-instructions.md) and several skills (brainstorm, review-pr, review-issue) still reference the old path, while newer skills (gather-project-knowledge, audit-project) use the new path. Functionally correct via symlink, but documentation is contradictory. Needs a cleanup pass.\n\n### Summary\n\n| Area | Status | Action |\n|------|--------|--------|\n| review-issue rename | Clean | None |\n| brainstorm value proposition | Addressed | None |\n| audit-project usefulness | Addressed | None |\n| Lifecycle documentation | Gap | #302 opened |\n| Path reference unification | Incomplete | Needs cleanup issue |\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Cod